and she suggested rib-eye steaks.

263
00:20:18,083 --> 00:20:21,211
- She said that's your favorite.
- I love my steak.

264
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:23,083
- Hi, Mike.

265
00:20:24,323 --> 00:20:26,188
Susan.

266
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:28,788
Edie.

267
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:31,624
I'm sorry about your house.
How are you?

268
00:20:31,697 --> 00:20:36,430
All right, I guess.
Oh, is somebody having a party?

269
00:20:36,501 --> 00:20:39,868
No, Susan's just throwing me
a traditional welcome dinner.

270
00:20:39,972 --> 00:20:43,339
Only I'm cooking.
And having it at my house.

271
00:20:44,710 --> 00:20:47,873
Traditional? Hm! I didn't get one.

272
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:49,914
Oh, it's a new tradition.

273
00:20:50,048 --> 00:20:53,449
It won't be anything fancy.
Just a little home cooking.

274
00:20:53,518 --> 00:20:55,509
Mm. That sounds so good.

275
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:59,546
